description: Karnataka CM Siddaramaiah's wife, Parvathi, has offered to surrender 14 plots allotted to her in Mysuru, citing her family's reputation as a priority. This decision follows allegations of nepotism and corruption against Siddaramaiah, leading to an FIR filed by Lokayukta police.
title: To save family's honour, Siddaramaiah's wife offers to return Muda plots

description: Amid fears of wider conflict in West Asia after Israel killed Hezbollah chief Hassan Nasrallah, PM Modi expressed solidarity against terrorism to Israeli PM Netanyahu. Modi also stressed preventing regional escalation and supported peace efforts, emphasizing humanitarian concerns in Gaza and the importance of restoring stability given India's interests in the region.
title: PM Modi speaks to Bibi, asks him not to escalate regional conflict

description: Bengaluru police arrested a Pakistani man, his Bangladeshi wife, and her parents for living in India for ten years using fake passports and Aadhaar cards. They were caught following a tip-off from Chennai immigration officials. Separately, the Army recovered three bodies from a 2019 crash site in the Chandra Bhaga mountains, identifying two soldiers and continuing the search for others.
title: Pak man, B'deshi wife, her parents living with fake IDs held near B'luru

description: A 26-year-old man in Gujarat's Navsari district is held for culpable homicide after he wasted time searching online remedies and attempted intercourse again, despite seeing his partner profusely bleeding post-sexual encounter. Authorities confirmed she eventually succumbed to excessive bleeding due to grave injuries. Police are investigating evidence destruction by the accused.
title: Girl bleeds to death as BF surfs net for hours looking for a remedy

description: Facing anti-incumbency, the BJP in Haryana has shifted its campaign focus from prominent leaders to the common people in its posters. The posters highlight government initiatives and welfare schemes, featuring faces of students, farmers, and women to reduce the impact of anti-incumbency ahead of the state elections.
title: In Haryana BJP posters, 'aam aadmi' takes centrestage ahead of polls

description: The Supreme Court admonished Andhra Pradesh CM N Chandrababu Naidu for publicly alleging without basis that adulterated ghee was used to make laddus at Tirumala Tirupati temple, causing distress among devotees. The bench questioned the state and TTD for proof and discussed the potential transfer of the investigation to an independent agency, seeking assistance from the solicitor general.
title: SC on laddu row: Keep gods away from politics

description: Enforcement Directorate is probing Karnataka CM Siddaramaiah and his wife for possible money laundering linked to a Mysore land allotment scam. This follows a complaint by an RTI activist and a high court order supporting an investigation. The ED has registered an ECIR and focused on the misuse of official powers and windfall gains for the CM’s wife.
title: ED initiates probe against Karnataka CM Siddaramaiah, wife in land case

description: Supreme Court has stated that the ongoing CBI probe into financial irregularities at RG Kar Medical College could extend to other medical institutions in West Bengal. The court expressed dissatisfaction with the state government's slow progress on installing CCTVs and improving facilities.
title: RG Kar graft probe may extend to other hospitals: SC

description: A CBI special court convicted retired SBI assistant general manager Jitendra Pratap Singh, his family members, and a CA in a 19-year-old disproportionate assets case. Singh received three years of rigorous imprisonment and a financial penalty, while his family and the CA were sentenced to one year in jail and fines. The assets were amassed through bogus accounts.
title: CBI court jails retired banker, 5 of family, CA in assets case

description: Climate activist Sonam Wangchuk and supporters are detained at Delhi's border during a peaceful march demanding environmental and constitutional rights for Ladakh. Rahul Gandhi condemns the detention, urging the government to listen to Ladakh's concerns and fulfill its promises made five years ago.
title: 'Unacceptable,' says Rahul Gandhi as Delhi police detains Sonam Wangchuk

description: The Maharashtra government has recognized indigenous cows as ‘Rajyamata-Gaumata’ due to their historical, nutritional, medicinal, and agricultural significance. In response to declining numbers, the cabinet will provide Rs 50 daily subsidies to cow shelters for better care of these breeds, aiming to support and preserve them.
title: Rajyamata-Gaumata title for desi cows, gaushalas to get subsidy: Maharashtra

description: Supreme Court issues notice to Assam government for contempt over demolitions and directs maintenance of status quo, following previous orders halting all demolitions without court approval to prevent misuse and uphold constitutional ethos.
title: SC orders status quo on Assam demolitions, issues notice

description: Three senior ministers rebuked Congress President Mallikarjun Kharge for his comment about outliving PM Narendra Modi and removing him from office. Despite his criticism, Modi checked on Kharge's health after his dizziness at a rally, showcasing a theme of political rivalry intertwined with personal interactions.
title: Kharge's remarks on PM Modi distasteful, disgraceful: Amit Shah

description: Amitabh Bachchan begins Kaun Banega Crorepati 16 with contestant Kirti from Uttar Pradesh. Kirti shares her father's dream of participating in KBC and her dedication to fulfilling it. She successfully advances without lifelines, discusses her inter-caste marriage, and highlights her father's unwavering love for KBC despite his illness.
title: KBC 16: Amitabh believes he is 'half-Sikh' recalling his maternal roots

description: In Haryana elections, tractors have become a symbol of rural appeal and agrarian interests, with their demand soaring and daily rent exceeding 1,000 rupees plus fuel. Political parties use tractors for campaign rallies, with star campaigners measuring influence by convoy length. Tractors' significant presence underscores their practicality for canvassing and connecting with rural voters.
title: In post-farm stir scenario, netas hitch poll wagons to tractors

description: India has observed a significant increase in its protected areas, with a 72% rise in the number and 16% growth in the total area from 2000 to 2023. Mangrove coverage also improved by 8% from 2013 to 2021. These updates highlight conservation efforts under the Wildlife (Protection) Act, 1972, and emphasize environmental data compiled under SEEA Framework.
title: Green data shows 72% rise in protected areas

description: Mithun Chakraborty, once involved with the Naxalites, overcame many challenges to receive Indian cinema's highest honor, the Dadasaheb Phalke award. His prolific career spans award-winning roles, commercial success, and contributions to social causes. Mithun also navigated the political spectrum, from extreme Red to BJP's saffron.
title: Mithun Chakraborty's life has more drama than most films

description: North Kashmir’s upcoming elections are pivotal, with Engineer Rashid's AIP facing accusations of being a BJP proxy and competing against NC and PC. Rashid’s past LS win and recent release have sparked debate, impacting voter sentiment and creating an unpredictable electoral outcome.
title: Pawn or kingmaker? Voters will decide Engineer Rashid fate today

description: An Army expedition has recovered four more bodies from the Antonov-12 aircraft that crashed near the Rohtang Pass in 1968. Identified military personnel include Sepoys Narayan Singh, Malkhan Singh, and Thomas Charan. The ongoing mission led by the Dogra Scouts, collaborating with Tiranga Mountain Rescue, continues to search for more remains in the snowbound mountains.
title: Army expedition recovers 4 more bodies from AN-12 crash near Rohtang Pass in '68

description: Britain has shut down its last coal-fired power station, marking an end to 142 years of coal reliance. The Ratcliffe-on-Soar plant ceased operations, symbolizing the UK's significant progress towards a cleaner energy future. The country has seen substantial growth in renewable energy, with coal now contributing a mere 1.8% to its electricity mix.
title: UK shuts down its last coal power station

description: According to a report, Segal asked 'who's drinking?' as he raised the toast. His fellow panelist Ben Caspit said he would but former Israeli military chief spokesperson Ronen Manelis apparently refused. “Really, everyone is happy that Nasrallah is dead,” Manelis said, as reported by New York Post. “[But] let’s think about the residents who had to flee their homes [due to the rocket bombardments].”​
title: Israeli journalist raises a toast on air on Hassan Nasrallah's death. Video viral

description: President Droupadi Murmu condemned the attacks on doctors, emphasizing such behavior is unacceptable. She acknowledged the limitations doctors face in medical science while highlighting their dedication and efforts, especially during the Covid-19 pandemic. Union health minister JP Nadda stressed compassionate patient communication to alleviate worries.
title: Attacks on doctors are unacceptable: President Droupadi Murmu

description: Mumbai's economic offences wing is investigating a complaint over alleged ticket fraud at a Coldplay concert. They questioned Big Tree Entertainment's COO Anil Makhija for four hours and have requested more documents. The company is accused of logging out genuine fans to create an artificial ticket queue.
title: Coldplay ‘ticket scalping’: EOW records portal COO statement

description: The DNA test revealed that SP functionary Moeed Khan, accused of raping a 12-year-old Ayodhya girl, did not match the fetus, but instead matched his domestic help, Raju Khan. The case, involving underage rape charges, sparked political controversy ahead of state assembly bypolls.
title: Ayodhya rape: DNA sample of fetus matches with SP man's servant, not his

description: Joe Flacco stepped in for injured Anthony Richardson and led the Indianapolis Colts to a 27-24 victory over the Pittsburgh Steelers, throwing two touchdowns for 168 yards. Despite Flacco's past success replacing injured quarterbacks, the Cleveland Browns did not offer him a contract this season. His performance raises questions about his future with the Colts.
title: Is Joe Flacco the unsung hero Colts needed all along

description: JD Vance versus Tim Walz is a high-stake debate because they have attacked and counter-attacked each other on several issues including what JD Vance called Tim Walz's 'stolen record'. JD Vance is a confident orator, debater and Tim Walz is reportedly anxious ahead of the debate fearing that he would let down Kamala Harris. But Walz's advantage is the political fumbles that the GOP made and many of them are credited to JD including the recent rumor of Haitians eating pets.
title: VP debate between JD Vance and Tim Walz: 10 things to know

description: Former England captain Michael Vaughan sparks controversy on social media by commenting that India is playing 'Bazball' during their aggressive batting in the second Test against Bangladesh. Indian fans rebuke, asserting their nation's long history of such play, crediting pioneers like Sehwag and Pant.
title: 'Bazball is a copycat product of ViruBall and...': Vaughan trolled

description: Adnaan Shaikh, former Bigg Boss OTT 3 contestant, faces legal trouble after his sister filed an FIR against him for allegedly beating her. A video shows her explaining the incident at Bangur Nagar police station. She sought activist Furkhan Shaikh's help, who initially advised resolving it privately but later accompanied her to file the complaint.
title: Bigg Boss OTT 3's Adnaan Shaikh's sister files an FIR against him: Reports
Maharashtra rains money on govt employees before poll code set in

description: Effective October 1, 2024, tnew TDS rates, including reductions for certain payments will come into effect. The Finance Bill has approved the following changes to the TDS rates, which will come into effect from October 1, 2024:
title: New TDS rates from Oct 1: What are revised tax deducted at source rates?

description: Defence minister Rajnath Singh addressed Congress president Mallikarjun Kharge's vow to stay alive until PM Modi is ousted, wishing Kharge a long life but backing Modi's leadership for 125 years. Singh criticized Congress for misgovernance in Himachal Pradesh and Karnataka, contrasting it with the corruption-free ten-year tenure of Modi's government.
title: 'I pray you live for 125 years': Rajnath responds to Kharge's statement

description: Popular Indian YouTuber Gaurav Taneja and his wife Ritu Rathee are addressing separation rumors. Taneja shared a message urging fans to respect their privacy, while a video shows Ritu seeking relationship advice, adding fuel to the rumors. Ritu later posted a video on Instagram urging people not to demonize one person in a relationship.
title: Video that may have led to Gaurav Taneja and Ritu Rathee's divorce rumours

description: Parvathi Siddaramaiah, wife of Karnataka CM Siddaramaiah, surrenders 14 MUDA compensation plots amid a money laundering investigation by the ED. The Congress accuses the central government of political harassment following their Karnataka electoral defeat. Siddaramaiah vows to fight the case legally.
title: Muda case: K'taka CM's wife offers to surrender 14 plots

description: Choi Soon-hwa, 81, a South Korean model, participated in the Miss Universe Korea pageant aiming to become its oldest contestant. Though she didn't win, she earned the 'Best Dresser' award. Choi began modeling in her 70s and joined the pageant after the age limit was lifted. Han Ariel, 22, won the pageant and will represent South Korea in Mexico.
title: 81-year-old South Korean narrowly misses out on becoming oldest Miss Universe

description: The Chief Electoral Officer of Haryana has recommended that authorities consider Gurmeet Ram Rahim Singh's request for 20-days emergency parole despite his controversial background. The recommendation follows a request citing his father's death anniversary. Singh's parole history and the upcoming state assembly elections, set for October 5, suggest political implications tied to his release.
title: Dera chief may get temporary release from jail on emergency parole
Why a study on adverse events in Covid jabs was withdrawn

description: On Gandhi Jayanti, various events and activities take place across the country. Schools, colleges, and organizations conduct discussions, prayers, and cultural programs reflecting Gandhi's ideals. The day is also observed as the International Day of Non-Violence, promoting peace and tolerance worldwide. By celebrating Gandhi Jayanti, we remember his legacy and reaffirm our commitment to his values of truth, non-violence, and justice.
title: Gandhi Jayanti 2024: Top 50 wishes, messages, and quotes to share

description: Navratri 2024 will be a vibrant celebration dedicated to Goddess Durga. Over nine nights, the festival brings together families and communities for prayers, cultural events, and joyous gatherings. Heartfelt wishes, messages, and quotes shared during this time highlight values of joy, prosperity, and the triumph of good over evil.
title: Happy Navratri 2024: Top 50 wishes, messages, and quotes to share with your loved ones

description: The final phase of polls in Jammu and Kashmir involves 40 constituencies, with major parties like the National Conference-Congress alliance, PDP, and BJP competing. The election gains significance as the first since Article 370's abrogation. Extensive preparations and security measures ensure a smooth voting process for 39 lakh eligible voters.
title: High-stakes in J&K polls phase 3: 415 candidates vie for 40 constituencies
Vikramaditya cites 'responsibility' to explain vendor nameplate diktat

description: Indian PM Modi spoke with Israeli PM Netanyahu regarding Israel's ongoing actions against Hezbollah. Modi emphasized that terrorism has no place in the world and stressed the importance of preventing regional escalation and ensuring the safe release of hostages. Nasrallah's death marks a significant shift in the Middle East power dynamics. ​​The potential disruption to this network could significantly weaken Iran's influence, reshuffling the region's balance of power.
title: 'Terrorism has no place in our world': PM Modi tells Israeli counterpart

description: WWE's Bad Blood 2024 PLE features highly anticipated matches like CM Punk vs. Drew McIntyre in a Hell in a Cell match and other championship bouts. The event takes place on October 5 at State Farm Arena, available on Peacock TV in the US and Sony LIV in India.
title: Bad Blood 2024: How to watch, date, full match card and more

description: The Supreme Court began hearings on the Kolkata rape-murder case and noted progress in the CBI investigation. The court directed the Ministry of Electronics to address social media leaks and criticized slow improvements in hospital facilities by the West Bengal government, setting deadlines for completion.
title: Kolkata case: SC slams Bengal govt over tardiness in implementing reforms

description: The Supreme Court of India defers the NEET PG 2024 examination case hearing to October 4 due to the absence of government counsel. Aspirants challenge last-minute changes to the exam format and demand transparency from NBEMS, leading to concerns about fairness and the normalization process.
title: No govt counsel, SC hearing on NEET-PG deferred to October 4

description: Jamie, an eight-year-old photographer from the UK, amazes netizens with her discovery of a rare pink grasshopper, caused by a genetic mutation. Her video detailing the encounter and scientific explanation goes viral, garnering praise for her enthusiasm and knowledge about nature.
title: UK's 8-year-old photographer spots rare pink grasshopper; video goes viral
'Gadkari's advice to investors reveals fiscal crisis in Maha'
Doctor leaves surgical needle inside head of girl

description: Israeli PM Benjamin Netanyahu addressed Iranians, criticizing their regime's neglect of health, education, and infrastructure, while diverting resources to war efforts. He expressed hope for a future where Israel and a free Iran coexist peacefully. Netanyahu also warned of escalating conflict between Israel and Iran-backed proxies following operations against Hezbollah leaders.
title: 'Fanatic theocrats leading you to abyss': Netanyahu warns Iranians

description: In a rain-affected second test in Kanpur, India overhauled Bangladesh’s total of 233 in just 28 overs, eventually declaring at 285-9. After reducing Bangladesh to 26-2 at stumps, India aimed for a win in a match heading for a draw. Exceptional performances included Rohit Sharma, Yashasvi Jaiswal, and bowlers like Ravichandran Ashwin.
title: 2nd Test, Day 4: India's batting lights up rain-hit B'desh clash

description: Congress president Mallikarjun Kharge and home minister Amit Shah engaged in a heated exchange over Kharge’s remarks on Prime Minister Modi. Shah condemned the comments as distasteful, while Kharge redirected focus to critical issues like Manipur and the caste census. This clash highlights rising political tensions ahead of key elections.
title: 'Focus on Manipur, not my health': Kharge slams Shah

description: A viral video shows a man doing pull-ups on a highway signboard 10 meters above the road in Amethi, Uttar Pradesh, endangering his life. The Amethi police have acknowledged the incident and are investigating. They have assured that appropriate legal action will follow against the individual after a thorough investigation.
title: Video of man doing pull-ups on signboard goes viral, UP police responds

description: The CBI is investigating 18 individuals, including 11 from Gujarat, accused of defrauding US citizens through call centres. Raids in multiple cities led to the seizure of digital evidence, cash, and luxury vehicles. The accused allegedly convinced victims to transfer funds using fake IRS investigations and tech support claims.
title: 11 Gujaratis operated con call centres to cheat US citizens: CBI

description: Former skipper Michael Vaughan likened India's aggressive first innings against Bangladesh to England's 'Bazball' approach. Openers Yashasvi Jaiswal and Rohit Sharma led India's high-scoring with quickfire knocks, aiming for a result after rain delays. With India's performance boosts their World Test Championship ambitions amidst future Tests against New Zealand and Australia.
title: 'India are playing Bazball': Ex-England captain on hosts' quickfire innings in Kanpur Test

description: International cricket stars, including Shamar Joseph and Naseem Shah, will feature in the upcoming SA20 auction with nearly 200 players vying for 13 spots across six franchises. Notable names like Martin Guptill and Reeza Hendricks headline the shortlist. The auction airs on October 1, ahead of the tournament starting January 9.
title: SA20 Auction: Players, squads, date - everything you need to know

description: The Enforcement Directorate filed a money-laundering case against Karnataka CM Siddaramaiah, linked to the Mysuru Urban Development Authority's land allotment irregularities. The case names Siddaramaiah’s wife, brother-in-law, and others, alleging compensatory plots were allocated to his wife in a high-value area. Siddaramaiah denies wrongdoing, calling the case politically motivated.
title: ED books K'taka CM in money-laundering case linked to Muda 'scam'

description: Israel's military marks a pivotal moment with the assassination of Hezbollah leader Hassan Nasrallah following an extensive campaign. The operation also included detonating communication devices and airstrikes, severely crippling Hezbollah. This event could destabilize Lebanon internally and alter regional power dynamics involving Iran and its allied militias. The question of whether Israel will launch a ground invasion into Lebanon looms large.
title: From pager blasts to Nasrallah’s killing: How Israel is creating a 'new Middle East'

description: WWE Superstar John Cena made his debut on Season 36 of The Simpsons, delivering Comic Book Guy and Kumiko Albertson's baby in a humorous scene. Known for his comedic roles, Cena’s appearance has generated excitement among fans as he transitions from wrestling to focus more on acting, promising more comic roles in the future.
title: WWE meets Springfield: John Cena delivers comic book Guy’s Baby

description: Tyler Huntley, nicknamed 'Snoop' for his high school resemblance to Snoop Dogg, has maintained his cool and collected persona throughout his football career. Despite changes in his physique, the name stuck, with teammates and fans embracing his laid-back style on the field.
title: Tyler Huntley’s 'snoop' nickname: The rapper connection explained

description: NASA reveals captivating images of the Sun, Orion Nebula, Eagle Nebula, Andromeda Galaxy, and Godzilla Nebula using advanced telescopes, showcasing their intricate structures and vibrant colors. These visuals provide unique insights into the dynamic nature of our celestial neighborhood, highlighting powerful solar activity and star formation regions.
title: Nasa’s stunning visuals of the sun, stars, galaxy, and stellar universe

description: Swiggy Instamart launches 24x7 free delivery in Delhi-NCR, offering rapid 10-15 minute delivery of groceries, festive treats, electronics, and more. This new service addresses late-night demand spikes, particularly during festive season preparations, with future expansion to other cities planned.
title: Swiggy Instamart launches 24/7 free delivery service in these cities

description: Virat Kohli narrowly escapes a run-out due to a miscommunication with Rishabh Pant during the second Test against Bangladesh. Half-centuries from Yashasvi Jaiswal and KL Rahul push India to 285 for nine. Shakib Al Hasan and Mehidy Hasan Miraz excel for Bangladesh with four wickets each.
title: Pant-Kohli hug after mix-up, Rohit's reaction caught on camera

description: Hackers are exploiting the names of trusted companies like Apple and Microsoft to defraud users, especially following new product launches. Using AI technology, these scams become harder to detect through deceptive pop-up messages and malvertising. Victims should change their passwords immediately and notify banks and law enforcement authorities about the scam.
title: How hackers are ‘using’ Apple and Microsoft to scam people online

description: Small finance banks are currently offering competitive interest rates on one-year fixed deposits, with Jana and Ujjivan Small Finance Banks leading at 8.25%. Investors should however be mindful of DICGC insurance limits and potential risks.
title: Banks offering up to 8.25% interest on FDs maturing in a year- check list

description: Air chief marshal Amar Preet Singh, with over 5,000 flying hours, assumed charge as the new Indian Air Force chief, succeeding Air Chief Marshal V R Chaudhari. With nearly 40 years of distinguished service, Singh's notable roles include commanding a fighter squadron, leading the MiG-29 upgrade project, and flight testing the LCA Tejas.
title: Air chief marshal A P Singh takes charge as new chief of air staff

description: Tata Advanced Systems Ltd secured a significant contract with the Moroccan defence forces to manufacture Wheeled Armoured Platform combat vehicles. Developed with the DRDO and Tata Motors, these indigenously designed vehicles will be delivered over three years, marking the largest international deal for Indian-made armoured vehicles.
title: Tata to build DRDO-developed armoured vehicles for Morocco armed forces

description: Rahul Gandhi criticised BJP's Agnipath scheme at a roadshow in Haryana, saying it would strip Agniveers of pensions to benefit Gautam Adani. The BJP countered, promising government jobs with pensions. ​In July, CM Nayab Singh Saini-led Haryana government announced a 10 per cent reservation for Agniveers in certain government jobs, besides age relaxation and interest-free loans for self-employment.
title: 'Pension will go into pocket of ...': Rahul sharpens attack against Agnipath scheme
Electoral bonds case: Relief for FM Sitharaman as K'taka HC stays probe

description: ​Latest post office small savings schemes interest rates Oct-Dec 2024: The rates of interest on various Small Savings Schemes for the third quarter of FY 2024-25 starting from 1st October, 2024 and ending on 31st December, 2024 shall remain unchanged.
title: Govt notifies latest post office schemes interest rates - check list

description: India has set a new benchmark in Test cricket by becoming the fastest team to score 200 runs in an innings, accomplishing this feat in just 24.2 overs. Openers Rohit Sharma and Yashasvi Jaiswal laid the foundation, while batting maestro Virat Kohli completed the milestone with a six against Bangladesh.
title: After fastest 50 & 100 in Tests, India surpass Australia to become...

description: The US Citizenship and Immigration Services (USCIS) has updated its policy manual to protect 'good faith' investors in the EB-5 program. This change aims to ensure that investors who comply with EB-5 rules are not disadvantaged due to misconduct by regional centers or other participants, preserving their path to permanent residency.
title: USCIS protects genuine investors in EB-5 green card program

description: BCCI vice-president Rajeev Shukla on Monday mentioned that the Indian government will determine if the national cricket team will visit Pakistan for the Champions Trophy next year, scheduled from February 19 to March 9. India and Pakistan have only faced each other in ICC events since bilateral cricket was halted in 2008 following security concerns.
title: Govt will decide on India's travel to Pak for CT: BCCI

description: Virat Kohli has achieved a significant milestone by becoming the fastest player to score 27,000 runs in international cricket, doing so in just 594 innings. This surpasses Sachin Tendulkar's previous record of 623 innings. Kohli reached this landmark during the fourth day of the second Test against Bangladesh in Kanpur, showcasing his remarkable consistency across all formats.
title: Kohli fastest to 27,000 runs in international cricket

description: The Supreme Court has mandated IIT Dhanbad to admit Atul Kumar, an 18-year-old Dalit student who missed the fee payment deadline by minutes. Exercising its power under Article 142, the court stressed that a talented student from a marginalized community should not lose his hard-earned seat due to financial constraints and directed the creation of an additional seat for him.
title: SC orders IIT Dhanbad to admit Dalit youth who lost seat over Rs 17K fees

description: India opener Yashasvi Jaiswal set new benchmarks for India on Day 4 of the second Test against Bangladesh in Kanpur. After hitting the fastest team fifty, he scored a rapid fifty off 31 balls and contributed to India's record-breaking fastest team hundred in Test cricket history, achieved in just 10.1 overs.
title: After fastest fifty, India smash fastest team hundred in Test cricket history

description: A fire occurred at Tata Electronics' Tamil Nadu factory, producing Apple iPhone components. The blaze originated in a chemical storage area and has been completely extinguished. Two workers were hospitalized but are expected to be discharged soon. Authorities have initiated a forensic investigation to determine the cause of the fire.
title: Fire at Tata's Apple factory: Tamil Nadu government begins investigation

description: From October 1, 2024, Indian stock market investors will encounter revised transaction fees from BSE and NSE, increased securities transaction tax on futures and options trading, and new taxation rules for share buybacks.
title: Stock market investing: Changes in transaction charges, STT, buyback taxation

description: PDP president Mehbooba Mufti called Israeli PM Benjamin Netanyahu the biggest terrorist, comparing him to Hitler. She disapproved of India's relationship with Israel due to its historical support for Palestine. Mufti criticized BJP over the Kathua rape case and expressed solidarity with Palestine and Lebanon following Hezbollah chief Nasrallah's death.
title: 'Netanyahu biggest terrorist after Hitler' says Mehbooba Mufti

description: The Supreme Court questioned Andhra Pradesh CM Chandrababu Naidu's claim about animal fat in Tirupati laddus, seeking proof and criticizing political involvement in religious matters. Concerns were raised over the report cited by the Andhra government, and the court considered whether an independent agency should handle the investigation.
title: 'Why go to press?' What SC told Andhra govt on Tirupati laddu row

description: The Maharashtra government has conferred the title 'Rajya Mata' on indigenous cows to boost their welfare. A new subsidy scheme offers Rs 50 per day for rearing these cows in goshalas. Managed by the Maharashtra Goseva Commission, this initiative seeks to support struggling goshalas and reverse the declining population of indigenous cows.
title: Maharashtra cabinet approves 'Rajya Mata' title for indigenous cows

description: Ravindra Jadeja secured his 300th Test wicket during the fourth day of the second Test against Bangladesh. This achievement makes him the seventh Indian bowler to reach this milestone, following greats like Anil Kumble and Kapil Dev. Notably, Jadeja is also the second fastest Indian to accomplish this feat based on balls delivered.
title: Jadeja reaches 300 Test wickets, 2nd quickest Indian by balls bowled

description: Indian openers Rohit Sharma and Yashasvi Jaiswal embarked on an aggressive mission against Bangladesh during the second Test at Green Park Stadium in Kanpur. Aiming for crucial World Test Championship points, they achieved a historic feat by scoring 50 runs within the first three overs, setting a new record for the fastest team fifty in Test cricket history.
title: India smash fastest team fifty in Test cricket history

description: The Supreme Court instructed Assam to maintain status quo on Sonapur demolitions and issued a notice following a contempt petition by residents. Emphasizing judicial oversight on using bulldozers as punitive tools, the Court allowed actions against encroachments on public land, including religious structures. The interim order remains valid until October 1.
title: 'Maintain status quo': SC issues contempt notice to Assam over demolition drive

description: The Indian government has warned investors about the rise in fraudulent activities on stock trading apps. PIB FactCheck cautions users against cybercriminals using fake profiles to scam people in stock trading groups. It advises verifying unknown identities before financial transactions and following safety tips to avoid falling victim to scams.
title: Government has ‘new scam alert’ on stock trading apps and platforms

description: In Noida, four people died and one was injured when an Alto car collided with a tractor on the Sector 10-11 road at around 2 AM. Five young men were returning from dinner when the accident occurred. Police have registered a case and are investigating the incident.
title: Noida road accident: Tractor-car collision claims 4 lives

description: The US has once again issued a record number of student visas in India this year, exceeding last year's figure of over 1.4 lakh. All first-time student applicants secured appointments at one of five consular sections in India. Indian students now represent the largest group of international graduate students in the US, constituting more than a quarter of foreign students.
title: US issues record student visas in India in 2024; fourth year in a row

description: Earth's gravity has captured a new temporary companion, Asteroid 2024 PT5, which is roughly the size of a bus. The mini moon will orbit Earth for about two months before breaking free on November 25. It is not visible to the naked eye and requires advanced telescopes for observation. The asteroid belongs to the Arjuna asteroid belt.
title: Earth has two moons now, but is the 'second moon' visible from India?

description: Subhani mosque authorities in Dharavi commenced demolishing unauthorised parts after BMC's G-North ward took action. The demolition, initially set for Sept 21, was postponed at the trustees' request. During the first attempt, three individuals were arrested for vandalising a BMC vehicle and causing traffic obstruction.
title: Trustees begin demolition of parts of Dharavi mosque

description: Ritu Rathee shared an Instagram video addressing divorce rumors with husband Gaurav Taneja.
title: ‘Not abla nari’: Ritu Rathee amidst rumours with YouTuber Gaurav Taneja

description: In October 2024, banks across several Indian states will observe closures for a total of 15 days due to various state-specific festivals and national holidays like Gandhi Jayanti, Dussehra, and Diwali. Additionally, banks will remain closed on all Sundays as well as the second and fourth Saturdays of the month.
title: Banks to be closed for up to 15 days in Oct: Check state-wise holiday list

description: Israeli forces launched airstrikes on Yemen's Ras Isa Port, targeting Houthi-controlled facilities in retaliation for recent missile attacks on Israel. The strikes caused multiple explosions and fires at oil tanks, killing four workers and injuring over 30 others. Ras Isa Port is a critical hub for Yemen's oil and humanitarian aid supplies.
title: Watch: Footage captures oil tank explosions in Yemen after Israeli strike

description: Industrialist S P Oswal was tricked into transferring Rs 7 crore by cybercriminals pretending to be CBI officers investigating Aadhaar misuse. Ludhiana Police arrested two suspects from Guwahati and recovered Rs 5.2 crore. The gang used fake arrest warrants and video calls in police uniforms to convince Oswal of the fraud, leading him to transfer the money.
title: Fake CBI cop, SC warrant: How Vardhman Group chairman lost Rs 7cr to online fraudsters

description: India showcased remarkable fielding on day four of the second Test against Bangladesh in Kanpur. Mohammed Siraj executed a spectacular one-handed catch to dismiss Shakib Al Hasan, while Rohit Sharma also took an impressive catch to dismiss Litton Das. These efforts delighted the Kanpur crowd following two days of washout.
title: Siraj's sensational catch in Kanpur leaves Shakib in disbelief

description: India is close to securing a deal with France for 26 Rafale Marine fighter jets for its aircraft carriers. The agreement will be discussed during NSA Ajit Doval's visit to Paris.
title: India close to finalising deal for 26 Rafale marine fighter jets

description: Congress expelled 10 leaders for six years due to anti-party activities, naming Chitra Sarwara and Satvinder Rana among others. BJP also removed eight leaders for running as independents in the upcoming Haryana assembly elections, including Ranjit Chautala and Devendra Kadyan. The elections are scheduled for October 5, with vote counting on October 8.
title: Congress expels 10 leaders in Haryana for indulging in anti-party activities

description: Severe flooding has hit several regions of Bihar due to heavy water release from the Kosi Barrage after intense rainfall. Floodwaters have reached the Katra Bakuchi Power Grid in Muzaffarpur, causing power outages for 45,000 homes. The situation has disrupted normal life, particularly in Supaul and Sitamarhi, with many homes inundated.
title: Bihar floods worsen as embankments of Kosi, Bagmati rivers breached

description: In the historic Eden Gardens Test between India and Australia, known for Harbhajan Singh's hat-trick and the partnership of VVS Laxman and Rahul Dravid, Sachin Tendulkar’s crucial bowling performance was pivotal. Taking three key wickets on Day 5, Tendulkar helped secure India's dramatic victory, ending Australia's record-winning streak of 16 consecutive Test matches.
title: 'Ek hi over...': When Tendulkar 'turned' the game in India's favour

description: A tragic incident unfolded in West Tripura where a 62-year-old woman was allegedly burnt alive by her two sons amid a suspected family dispute. The event occurred on Saturday night in Khamarbari. Authorities have arrested the sons and launched an investigation. The woman had been residing with them after losing her husband one-and-a-half years ago.
title: 62-year-old woman tied to tree and burnt alive by sons in Tripura

description: Chief Justice of India DY Chandrachud reprimanded a petitioner for using informal language in the Supreme Court, stressing that it is not a coffee shop. This incident follows another where he ordered security to remove senior advocate Mathews Nedumpara during a NEET-UG hearing for interrupting proceedings and addressing the gallery without permission.
title: 'Don't say yeah yeah yeah': CJI Chandrachud reprimands lawyer in SC

description: Posters have been placed around Delhi's ITO area, blaming the BJP for a spike in shooting incidents. Over the past 24 hours, three shootings occurred in the city. The posters accuse the BJP of making Delhi a 'capital of gangsters,' citing recent attacks on businesses in West Delhi as evidence.
title: Watch: Posters blaming BJP for surge in shooting incidents surface in Delhi

description: Prince Harry recently honored his late mother, Princess Diana, at the 2024 Concordia Annual Summit. He spoke about their special bond and commended Dr. Tessy OJo and Diana Award winners for their dedication to humanitarian efforts. Harry emphasized the importance of continuing Diana's philanthropic work to keep her memory alive.
title: 'My mum ... ': Prince Harry's tribute for mother Princess Diana

description: Rohit Sharma thrilled spectators at the Green Park Stadium during day four of the Kanpur Test with an impressive one-handed catch, dismissing Litton Das during the morning session. This highlight came after two days of rain. India lead the series 1-0, following a commanding win in Chennai by 280 runs.
title: Rohit Sharma's one-handed stunner lights up Kanpur

description: Mithun Chakraborty will be honoured with a Dadasaheb Phalke Award for his contribution to Indian cinema. The ceremony will take place on October 8.
title: Mithun Chakraborty to be honoured with Dabasaheb Phalke Award

description: US Senator Mark Kelly disclosed that Israel utilized a US-manufactured 2,000-lb Mark 84 series bomb to eliminate Hezbollah leader Hassan Nasrallah. The White House was not pre-informed about the airstrike. This move comes after Hezbollah allied with Hamas in Gaza, leading to the deaths of seven top commanders, including Nasrallah.
title: Israel used 900kg American-made bomb to eliminate Nasrallah: Report

description: Union Home Minister Amit Shah criticized Congress President Mallikarjun Kharge for his statement about not dying until PM Modi is removed from power. This comment was made after Kharge fell ill during a speech in Jammu and Kashmir. Shah termed the remark distasteful and wished Kharge a long, healthy life.
title: 'May he live to ... ': Shah slams Kharge for remark on PM after health scare

description: Ashneer Grover has finalized a settlement with BharatPe, ceasing all associations with the company amid accusations of fund misappropriation.
title: Ashneer Grover makes 'peace' with BharatPe, read ‘settlement post’

description: The IPL Governing Council has brought back the 'uncapped' player retention rule, which allows franchises to retain two Indian players who haven't played international cricket or held a central contract for five years. This move benefits Chennai Super Kings by enabling them to retain MS Dhoni for the 2025 season. A few other former India players also qualify to be considered 'uncapped'.
title: EXPLAINED: Is uncapped IPL player rule designed for Dhoni?

description: A vigilant driver of the Pushpak Express prevented a possible train accident on the Jhansi-Kanpur route by spotting and stopping for a fire extinguisher on the tracks. The cylinder, identified as railway property from Gorakhpur's Kushinagar Express, had accidentally fallen off. Railway authorities are investigating to determine further actions.
title: Alert loco pilot averts tragedy after spotting fire extinguisher on rail tracks

description: Israel has significantly escalated its actions against Hezbollah by killing seven top commanders, including leader Hassan Nasrallah. This move follows Hezbollah's alliance with Hamas in Gaza. The deaths present a major challenge for the organization. The group's Shura Council is expected to meet soon to select new leadership.
title: Nasrallah to Nabil Kaouk: 7 Hezbollah commanders killed in Israeli strikes in 7 days

description: US President Joe Biden has urged for efforts to prevent an all-out war in the Middle East amid rising tensions between Israel and Hezbollah. Following Israeli airstrikes that killed Hezbollah leader Hassan Nasrallah, Biden expressed worries about potential involvement from Iran and the US. He plans to communicate with Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu soon.
title: Could an all-out war in the Middle East be avoided? What Biden said

description: Fake notes with Anupam Kher's face on it with 'Resole Bank Of India' printed on them, instead of 'Reserve Bank Of India' were seized in Gujrat. These fake notes were worth Rs 1.60 crore.
title: Fake currency notes with Anupam Kher's picture siezed in Gujarat

description: Sean "Diddy" Combs is no longer under intensive monitoring at Brooklyn's detention center where he faces sexual assault and prostitution charges. Despite being denied bail twice, including a $50 million offer, Combs remains focused on his legal defense. His family has surrendered their passports to support his claim of not being a flight risk.
title: Sean 'Diddy' Combs taken 'off suicide watch' as court trial looms

description: In Rwanda, Marburg virus disease has resulted in six fatalities, mainly among healthcare workers. The virus, which causes hemorrhagic fever, spreads through contact with bodily fluids. Authorities urge preventive measures such as maintaining hygiene and avoiding contact with infected individuals. Currently, there is no specific treatment available; supportive care remains essential for managing symptoms.
title: Marburg virus in circulation: Can it start another pandemic?

description: Rohit Sharma and his teammates from India's T20 World Cup-winning team will be seen on Season 2 of 'The Great Indian Kapil Show' on Netflix. In a promo clip, Rohit's famous forgetfulness was funnily pointed by actress Archana Puran Singh. Suryakumar Yadav, Arshdeep Singh, Shivam Dube and Axar Patel also feature in the episode.
title: 'Team India ka Ghajini kaun hai?' - Rohit Sharma answers

description: Israel launched new airstrikes in Lebanon's Bekaa region, focusing on Hezbollah targets after a deadly day of strikes that killed over 105 people. The Israeli Defense Forces aim to weaken Hezbollah’s military infrastructure. Recent operations have led to the deaths of several high-ranking leaders and displaced over 200,000 people in Lebanon.
title: Watch: Israel's fighter jets continue to attack dozens of Hezbollah targets

description: YouTube has removed music videos from several high-profile artists, including Adele and Kanye West, amid a licensing dispute with SESAC. Users are encountering messages that the content is unavailable in their country. YouTube aims for a swift resolution through ongoing negotiations with SESAC to restore access.
title: Why YouTube has taken down music videos from Kanye West, Britney Spears & others

description: The article gives daily numerology predictions for individuals according to their birth dates. It details the unique challenges and opportunities each number will face today, highlighting the importance of diplomacy, creativity, patience, and emotional balance. Readers are urged to navigate their day with mindfulness and a cooperative attitude.
title: Numerology predictions today: Read your personalised forecast for numbers 1 to 9

description: The 22-year-old fast bowler Mayank Yadav has been selected for India's T20I series against Bangladesh. Despite limited experience, his ability to bowl over 150 kmph impressed selectors. He credits Sonnet Club and mentors like Gautam Gambhir and Morne Morkel for their support in his development and overcoming injuries. He played for the Lucknow Super Giants in IPL 2024.
title: 'Before IPL, I was not aware I could bowl so quick' - Mayank Yadav
23 terror hits in J&K so far this year, down from 222 in 2014
FPIs buy Rs 57k crore stocks in September, flows hit 9-month high
I-T raids on loan agent raise kickback concerns

description: Karan Veer, the winner of Khatron Ke Khiladi 14, expressed immense joy and surprise at his victory. He found the journey enriching and fun. Although he anticipates more opportunities and possibly higher payments, Karan intends to keep portraying diverse characters in his career.
title: Exclusive - Khatron Ke Khiladi 14: Karan Veer Mehra lifts trophy
Rejigged monetary policy committee may not alter status quo

description: An Israeli airstrike targeted an apartment building in Beirut, killing at least two people and heightening regional tensions. This incident follows recent strikes on Hezbollah and Houthi positions. Over 1,000 Lebanese have died recently, with a million displaced. The US is advocating for diplomatic resolutions to avoid further conflict.
title: Israel hit Beirut city limits for first time, also struck Houthis in Yemen

description: The IPL Player Regulations are out, and franchises can now decide on player retentions. Mohammad Kaif has advised Royal Challengers Bengaluru to appoint Rohit Sharma as captain in place of Virat Kohli. Kaif argues that Rohit's leadership could end RCB's wait for an IPL title, highlighting his ability to get the best out of players.
title: 'Bhai le lo Rohit Sharma ko as a captain': Expert advice to RCB

description: Pakistan all-rounder Iftikhar Ahmed, upset after his team's defeat in the Champions Cup final, criticized the media for hyping young talent prematurely. He urged that young players should prove themselves in domestic cricket on a consistent basis before being talked about as a prospect for the national team.
title: 'Cricket ka sara mahaul kharab': Pakistan batsman gets angry
Dera chief again seeks parole; Give reasons, EC tells Haryana
Two Jaipur heritage sites shut for 2 days to wipe out rodents
Govt block on account of ‘Hindutva Watch’ not justified, X tells Delhi HC
'AI' washing machine to smart TV: Premium carts drive festive sales

description: Two Meitei youths from Thoubal district disappeared after attending a recruitment test in Imphal West, Manipur. Allegedly abducted by Kuki militants, their case has drawn attention from CM N Biren Singh, who is focusing on their rescue. A third youth has been found safe, and efforts are ongoing to locate the remaining two.
title: Manipur CM Biren accuses Kuki militants of abducting 2 Manipuri youths

description: An animal husbandry official from Banaskantha has filed a police complaint against three vigilantes who allegedly assaulted him and his staff, accusing them of cow slaughter. The incident took place at a goat-breeding facility, where the attackers also used caste-based slurs and confined the officials for four hours before fleeing when police were called.
title: ‘Gaurakshaks’ attack staffers at Gujarat goat breeding centre

description: Campaigning for the final phase of J&K assembly elections ended peacefully, covering 40 segments across seven districts with heightened security due to recent terrorist activities. Key candidates include Ajaz Ahmad Guru and Sajad Gani Lone. This election is the first since Article 370's abrogation, featuring fierce competition among BJP, Congress-NC alliance, and PDP.
title: Campaign for J&K’s final phase ends

description: During a public speech in Nagpur, Shiv Sena (UBT) chief Uddhav Thackeray criticized the BJP for conspiring against him and selling assets to Gautam Adani. He challenged Union minister Amit Shah to make his plans public. Thackeray also accused the BJP of fake Hindutva ideology and questionable land deals involving their allies.
title: 'Do you agree with BJP’s Hindutva?': Uddhav's salvo at RSS chief

description: Tamil Nadu Chief Minister M K Stalin declared that his son Udhayanidhi has been made deputy CM to serve the people and advance the state's development. Stalin commended Udhayanidhi's progress in sports and youth engagement. He also defended Senthil Balaji, describing his imprisonment as a sacrifice due to conspiracies against DMK.
title: I made Udhayanidhi my deputy to assist people, not me: TN CM Stalin

description: Horoscope Today: Read daily horoscope predictions for September 30, 2024. Know all about the astrological events and influences that will be affecting each of the 12 zodiac signs. Get ready to discover what the stars have in store for you today.
title: Horoscope today: Read your today's astrological predictions
